



Sir
War Office, Williamsburg December 1. 1779.



We enclose Mr. Dicksons application to us, to annex a Salary to his Office. Conceiving it out of our Province to say what shall be his allowance, we take liberty to refer the Settlement of that matter, to your Honorable Board. We shall only beg leave to add that the Office of Cloathier is a very laborious and important One, [210] the duties of which we can venture to assure your Excellency, Mr. Dickson has ever performed with Integrity and assiduity. We have the Honor to be Your Excellencys


jas. innes wm. nelson saml. griffin


